I89. Definitions

I11In this chapter, the following definitions apply:

I12(1) T4Unit of general local governmentK._The term ``unit of general local government'' means a city, county, town, parish, village, or other general-purpose political subdivision of a State.

I12(2) T4Urban areaK._The term ``urban area'' means_

I13(A) a geographical area within the jurisdiction of an incorporated city, town, borough, village, or other unit of general local government, except a county or parish, having a population of at least 10,000 inhabitants;

I13(B) that portion of the geographical area within the jurisdiction of a county, town, township, or similar governmental entity which contains no incorporated unit of general local government but has a population density of at least 1,500 inhabitants per square mile; and

I13(C) that portion of a geographical area having a population density of at least 1,500 inhabitants per square mile and situated adjacent to the boundary of an incorporated unit of general local government which has a population of at least 10,000.

