I89. Definitions and nonapplication

I11(a) T4DefinitionsK._In this chapter_

I12(1) T4AlterK._The term ``alter'' includes_

I13(A) preliminary planning, engineering, architectural, legal, fiscal, and economic investigations and studies, surveys, designs, plans, working drawings, specifications, procedures, and other similar actions necessary for the alteration of a public building; and

I13(B) repairing, remodeling, improving, or extending, or other changes in, a public building.

Q04

I12(2) T4ConstructK._The term ``construct'' includes preliminary planning, engineering, architectural, legal, fiscal, and economic investigations and studies, surveys, designs, plans, working drawings, specifications, procedures, and other similar actions necessary for the construction of a public building.

I12(3) T4Executive agencyK._The term ``executive agency'' means an executive department or independent establishment in the executive branch of the Federal Government, including_

I13(A) any wholly owned Government corporation;

I13(B) the Central-Bank for Cooperatives and the regional banks for cooperatives;

I13(C) federal land banks;

I13(D) federal intermediate credit banks;

I13(E) the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation; and

I13(F) the Government National Mortgage Association.

Q04

I12(4) T4Federal agencyK._The term ``federal agency'' means an executive agency or an establishment in the legislative or judicial branch of the Government (except the Senate, the House of Representatives, and the Architect of the Capitol and any activities under the direction of the Architect).

I12(5) T4Public buildingK._The term ``public building''_

I13(A) means a building, whether for single or multitenant occupancy, and its grounds, approaches, and appurtenances, which is generally suitable for use as office or storage space or both by one or more federal agencies or mixed-ownership Government corporations;

I13(B) includes_

I14(i) federal office buildings;

I14(ii) post offices;

I14(iii) customhouses;

I14(iv) courthouses;

I14(v) appraisers stores;

I14(vi) border inspection facilities;

I14(vii) warehouses;

I14(viii) record centers;

I14(ix) relocation facilities;

I14(x) telecommuting centers;

I14(xi) similar federal facilities; and

I14(xii) any other buildings or construction projects the inclusion of which the President considers to be justified in the public interest; but

Q04

I13(C) does not include a building or construction project described in subparagraphs (A) and (B)_

I14(i) that is on the public domain (including that reserved for national forests and other purposes);

I14(ii) that is on property of the Government in foreign countries;

I14(iii) that is on Indian and native Eskimo property held in trust by the Government;

I14(iv) that is on land used in connection with federal programs for agricultural, recreational, and conservation purposes, including research in connection with the programs;

I14(v) that is on or used in connection with river, harbor, flood control, reclamation or power projects, for chemical manufacturing or development projects, or for nuclear production, research, or development projects;

I14(vi) that is on or used in connection with housing and residential projects;

I14(vii) that is on military installations (including any fort, camp, post, naval training station, airfield, proving ground, military supply depot, military school, or any similar facility of the Department of Defense);

I14(viii) that is on installations of the Department of Veterans Affairs used for hospital or domiciliary purposes; or

I14(ix) the exclusion of which the President considers to be justified in the public interest.

Q04

