I89. Supplements to federal grant programs

I11(a) T4Definition._

I12(1) T4Federal grant programsK._In this section, the term ``federal grant programs''_

I13(A) means any federal grant program that provides assistance for the acquisition or development of land, the construction or equipment of facilities, or other community or economic development or economic adjustment activities, including a federal grant program authorized by_

I14(i) the Consolidated Farm and Rural Development Act (7 U.S.C. 1921 et seq.);

I14(ii) the Land and Water Conservation Fund Act of 1965 (16 U.S.C. 460T3lKÿ094 et seq.);

I14(iii) the Watershed Protection and Flood Prevention Act (16 U.S.C. 1001 et seq.);

I14(iv) the Carl D. Perkins Career and Technical Education Act of 2006 (20 U.S.C. 2301 et seq.);

I14(v) the Federal Water Pollution Control Act (33 U.S.C. 1251 et seq.) (known as the Clean Water Act);

I14(vi) title VI of the Public Health Services Act (42 U.S.C. 291 et seq.);

I14(vii) sections 201 and 209 of the Public Works and Economic Development Act of 1965 (42 U.S.C. 3141, 3149);

I14(viii) title I of the Housing and Community Development Act of 1974 (42 U.S.C. 5301 et seq.); and

I14(ix) part IV of title III of the Communications Act of 1934 (47 U.S.C. 390 et seq.); but

