I89. Definitions

I11In this subtitle, the following definitions apply:

I12(1) T4CommissionK._The term ``Commission'' means a Commission established under section 15301.

I12(2) T4Local development districtK._The term ``local development district'' means an entity that_

I13(A)(i) is an economic development district that is_

I14(I) in existence on the date of the enactment of this chapter; and

I14(II) located in the region; or

Q04

I13(ii) if an entity described in clause (i) does not exist_

I14(I) is organized and operated in a manner that ensures broad-based community participation and an effective opportunity for local officials, community leaders, and the public to contribute to the development and implementation of programs in the region;

I14(II) is governed by a policy board with at least a simple majority of members consisting of_

I16(aa) elected officials; or

I16(bb) designees or employees of a general purpose unit of local government that have been appointed to represent the unit of local government; and

Q04

I14(III) is certified by the Governor or appropriate State officer as having a charter or authority that includes the economic development of counties, portions of counties, or other political subdivisions within the region; and

Q04

I13(B) has not, as certified by the Federal Cochairperson_

I14(i) inappropriately used Federal grant funds from any Federal source; or

I14(ii) appointed an officer who, during the period in which another entity inappropriately used Federal grant funds from any Federal source, was an officer of the other entity.

Q04

I12(3) T4Federal grant programK._The term ``Federal grant program'' means a Federal grant program to provide assistance in carrying out economic and community development activities.

I12(4) T4Indian tribeK._The term ``Indian tribe'' has the meaning given the term in section 4 of the Indian Self-Determination and Education Assistance Act (25 U.S.C. 450b).

I12(5) T4Nonprofit entityK._The term ``nonprofit entity'' means any organization described in section 501(c) of the Internal Revenue Code of 1986 and exempt from taxation under 501(a) of that Code that has been formed for the purpose of economic development.

I12(6) T4RegionK._The term ``region'' means the area covered by a Commission as described in subchapter II of chapter 157.\1\N

