I89. Establishment, membership, and employees

I11(a) T4EstablishmentK._There are established the following regional Commissions:

I12(1) The Southeast Crescent Regional Commission.

I12(2) The Southwest Border Regional Commission.

I12(3) The Northern Border Regional Commission.

Q04

I11(b) T4Membership._

I12(1) T4Federal and state membersK._Each Commission shall be composed of the following members:

I13(A) A Federal Cochairperson, to be appointed by the President, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate.

I13(B) The Governor of each participating State in the region of the Commission.

Q04

I12(2) T4Alternate members._

I13(A) T4Alternate federal cochairpersonK._The President shall appoint an alternate Federal Cochairperson for each Commission. The alternate Federal Cochairperson, when not actively serving as an alternate for the Federal Cochairperson, shall perform such functions and duties as are delegated by the Federal Cochairperson.

I13(B) T4State alternatesK._The State member of a participating State may have a single alternate, who shall be appointed by the Governor of the State from among the members of the Governor's cabinet or personal staff.

I13(C) T4VotingK._An alternate member shall vote in the case of the absence, death, disability, removal, or resignation of the Federal or State member for which the alternate member is an alternate.

Q04

I12(3) T4CochairpersonsK._A Commission shall be headed by_

I13(A) the Federal Cochairperson, who shall serve as a liaison between the Federal Government and the Commission; and

I13(B) a State Cochairperson, who shall be a Governor of a participating State in the region and shall be elected by the State members for a term of not less than 1 year.

Q04

I12(4) T4Consecutive termsK._A State member may not be elected to serve as State Cochairperson for more than 2 consecutive terms.

Q04

I11(c) T4Compensation._

I12(1) T4Federal cochairpersonsK._Each Federal Cochairperson shall be compensated by the Federal Government at level III of the Executive Schedule as set out in section 5314 of title 5.

I12(2) T4Alternate federal cochairpersonsK._Each Federal Cochairperson's alternate shall be compensated by the Federal Government at level V of the Executive Schedule as set out in section 5316 of title 5.

I12(3) T4State members and alternatesK._Each State member and alternate shall be compensated by the State that they represent at the rate established by the laws of that State.

Q04

I11(d) T4Executive Director and Staff._

I12(1) T4In generalK._A Commission shall appoint and fix the compensation of an executive director and such other personnel as are necessary to enable the Commission to carry out its duties. Compensation under this paragraph may not exceed the maximum rate of basic pay established for the Senior Executive Service under section 5382 of title 5, including any applicable locality-based comparability payment that may be authorized under section 5304(h)(2)(C) of that title.

I12(2) T4Executive directorK._The executive director shall be responsible for carrying out the administrative duties of the Commission, directing the Commission staff, and such other duties as the Commission may assign.

Q04

I11(e) T4No Federal Employee StatusK._No member, alternate, officer, or employee of a Commission (other than the Federal Cochairperson, the alternate Federal Cochairperson, staff of the Federal Cochairperson, and any Federal employee detailed to the Commission) shall be considered to be a Federal employee for any purpose.

