I89. Decisions

I11(a) T4Requirements for ApprovalK._Except as provided in section 15304(c)(3), decisions by the Commission shall require the affirmative vote of the Federal Cochairperson and a majority of the State members (exclusive of members representing States delinquent under section 15304(c)(3)(C)).

I11(b) T4ConsultationK._In matters coming before the Commission, the Federal Cochairperson shall, to the extent practicable, consult with the Federal departments and agencies having an interest in the subject matter.

I11(c) T4QuorumsK._A Commission shall determine what constitutes a quorum for Commission meetings; except that_

I12(1) any quorum shall include the Federal Cochairperson or the alternate Federal Cochairperson; and

I12(2) a State alternate member shall not be counted toward the establishment of a quorum.

Q04

I11(d) T4Projects and Grant ProposalsK._The approval of project and grant proposals shall be a responsibility of each Commission and shall be carried out in accordance with section 15503.

