I89. Economic and infrastructure development grants

I11(a) T4In GeneralK._A Commission may make grants to States and local governments, Indian tribes, and public and nonprofit organizations for projects, approved in accordance with section 15503_

I12(1) to develop the transportation infrastructure of its region;

I12(2) to develop the basic public infrastructure of its region;

I12(3) to develop the telecommunications infrastructure of its region;

I12(4) to assist its region in obtaining job skills training, skills development and employment-related education, entrepreneurship, technology, and business development;

I12(5) to provide assistance to severely economically distressed and underdeveloped areas of its region that lack financial resources for improving basic health care and other public services;

I12(6) to promote resource conservation, tourism, recreation, and preservation of open space in a manner consistent with economic development goals;

I12(7) to promote the development of renewable and alternative energy sources; and

I12(8) to otherwise achieve the purposes of this subtitle.

Q04

I11(b) T4Allocation of FundsK._A Commission shall allocate at least 40 percent of any grant amounts provided by the Commission in a fiscal year for projects described in paragraphs (1) through (3) of subsection (a).

I11(c) T4Sources of GrantsK._Grant amounts may be provided entirely from appropriations to carry out this subtitle, in combination with amounts available under other Federal grant programs, or from any other source.

I11(d) T4Maximum Commission Contributions._

I12(1) T4In generalK._Subject to paragraphs (2) and (3), the Commission may contribute not more than 50 percent of a project or activity cost eligible for financial assistance under this section from amounts appropriated to carry out this subtitle.

I12(2) T4Distressed countiesK._The maximum Commission contribution for a project or activity to be carried out in a county for which a distressed county designation is in effect under section 15702 may be increased to 80 percent.

I12(3) T4Special rule for regional projectsK._A Commission may increase to 60 percent under paragraph (1) and 90 percent under paragraph (2) the maximum Commission contribution for a project or activity if_

I13(A) the project or activity involves 3 or more counties or more than one State; and

I13(B) the Commission determines in accordance with section 15302(a) that the project or activity will bring significant interstate or multicounty benefits to a region.

Q04

I11(e) T4Maintenance of EffortK._Funds may be provided by a Commission for a program or project in a State under this section only if the Commission determines that the level of Federal or State financial assistance provided under a law other than this subtitle, for the same type of program or project in the same area of the State within region, will not be reduced as a result of funds made available by this subtitle.

I11(f) T4No Relocation AssistanceK._Financial assistance authorized by this section may not be used to assist a person or entity in relocating from one area to another.

