I89. Local development districts and organizations

I11(a) T4Grants to Local Development DistrictsK._Subject to the requirements of this section, a Commission may make grants to a local development district to assist in the payment of development planning and administrative expenses.

I11(b) T4Conditions for Grants._

I12(1) T4Maximum amountK._The amount of a grant awarded under this section may not exceed 80 percent of the administrative and planning expenses of the local development district receiving the grant.

I12(2) T4Maximum period for state agenciesK._In the case of a State agency certified as a local development district, a grant may not be awarded to the agency under this section for more than 3 fiscal years.

I12(3) T4Local shareK._The contributions of a local development district for administrative expenses may be in cash or in kind, fairly evaluated, including space, equipment, and services.

Q04

I11(c) T4Duties of Local Development DistrictsK._A local development district shall_

I12(1) operate as a lead organization serving multicounty areas in the region at the local level;

